Semiconductor Grade Phenolic Resin Market Overview
The global phenolic resin market was valued at USD 11.7 billion in 2021 and is projected to reach USD 14.4 billion by 2026, growing at a CAGR of 4.3% from 2021 to 2026.

Phenolic resins are thermosetting polymers synthesized from phenol and formaldehyde, known for their high heat resistance, mechanical strength, and flame retardancy. These properties make them essential in various industries, including automotive, construction, electronics, and consumer goods. The market is categorized into types such as resol and novolac resins, and applications including wood adhesives, molding compounds, insulation materials, laminates, paper impregnation, and coatings.

